{"comments":"Blackwell Approachability for Online Learning.\n\n## Theoretical Foundation\n\nBlackwell's theorem: For a repeated game with vector payoffs, if the\ntarget set S is response-satisfiable, there exists a strategy that\nmakes the average payoff converge to S.\n\nWe use this to achieve first-order regret bounds by making regret\na component of the vector payoff.\n\n## References\n\n- Blackwell, D. \"An Analog of the Minimax Theorem for Vector Payoffs\"\n  Pacific J. Math. 6(1), 1-8 (1956)\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- Data.Array (replicate, mapWithIndex, index)\n","declarations":[{"children":[{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Record"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["avgPayoff",{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Array"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["dualVariable",{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Array"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["dimension",{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Int"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["rounds",{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Int"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"tag":"REmpty"}],"tag":"RCons"}],"tag":"RCons"}],"tag":"RCons"}],"tag":"RCons"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[79,4],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Optimize/Submodular/Online/Blackwell.purs","start":[67,24]},"title":"BlackwellState"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Eq"],"Eq"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Optimize","Submodular","Online","Blackwell"],"BlackwellSt